Create these files before a live deployment. Never commit their values:

- postgres_bootstrap_password (database bootstrap only; at least 32 non-whitespace characters)
- postgres_owner_password (migration/model owner; a different value)
- postgres_api_password (least-privilege API role; a different value)
- postgres_worker_password (least-privilege Worker/River role; a different value)
- legnext_api_key
- openrouter_api_key
- provider_callback_secret (at least 32 random bytes, URL-safe)
- provider_url_signing_secret (a different value, at least 32 random bytes)
- grafana_admin_password (required only for the observability profile)
- alertmanager_webhook_url (required only for the alerting profile; exactly one HTTPS URL)

The four database passwords must be generated independently and must not be
stored in `.env`, `DATABASE_URL`, command arguments, or `.pgpass`. The callback
and URL-signing secrets must never reuse a provider API key or each other.

Compose mounts file-backed secrets without remapping ownership. Set the four
database secrets, both provider keys, and both internal signing secrets to host
owner `65532:65532` and mode `0600`. Set `grafana_admin_password` to owner
`472:472` and mode `0600`; set `alertmanager_webhook_url` to owner
`65534:65534` and mode `0600`. The host root user and Docker daemon can still
read these files for controlled backup and deployment operations.
